9... Ne4 10. Qc2 dxc4 { White has to lose time now by recapturing on c4. } 11.
Bxc4 c5 { Immediately attacking the center! } 12. O-O Nd7
{ With a perfectly equal position. We'll follow up with Rc8, creating an unpleasant x-ray on the c-file. We might then take on d4 when White is forced to either go for an inferior isolated pawn structure or leave the long light diagonal vulnerable by recapturing with the f3-knight. }
