{ Leaving the x-ray on the long diagonal  @@StartBracket@@just in case White manages to play e4@@EndBracket@@. It's also a useful move for our b4-plan. }
16. Nc5 Bc8
{ The bishop is no longer effectively placed on the long light diagonal, so we reroute it to a better position. A good square for it would be f5, for example. We may follow up with Na5-Nc4. }
