{ Realizing that Black is going to play on the kingside, White tries to organize their counterplay on the queenside. }
11... Be7 12. b4
{ White plans to play c5, threatening c6. In case we meet c5 with c6 ourselves, b5 might follow... }
12... c6
{ A prophylactical move.  13.c5  will be met with  13...b5  , sealing the queenside. }
13. Qb3 { X-raying Black's king. } 13... Kh8
{ Another prophylactical move. It's very important not to forget about the opponent's threats. There will be enough time for attacking on the kingside after we secure the center and the queenside. }
14. Rfd1 Qe8
{ The queen is heading to h5 and then our attack on the kingside will begin. Ideas like f4 or Ndf6-Ng4 or even g5-g4 will follow.   See the gameBok - Le Quang, 2019, St.Louis, 0-1. }
