5... Bxd2+
{ Black's plan will be similar after all of the captures. After castling, we'll play d6, then e5, and, depending on what White will do about their pawn structure in the center, we'll choose our plan accordingly. }
6. Nbxd2
{ The mainline, though it looks to me that the knight is not as happy on d2 as it would be on c3, from where it would not only control e4 but also d5. }
6... d6
{ White has a few options here, though all of them will be met by the same reaction: short castle followed by e5. We already have a feel of this pawn structure and now we'll see the possible plans. }
7. e4 e5
{ Once again, White faces a choice on how to handle the pawn structure in the center. They can close it with d5, take on e5 or wait a bit by defending the e4-pawn. }
8. d5 a5
{ As the knight is placed on d2 rather than on c3, Black threatens to play a4, making it impossible for White to make any progress on the queenside. Another positive aspect of our a4-threat is that it would secure the very nice c5-square for our b8-knight. }
9. b4 { Not allowing a4 and trying to make c5 happen as fast as possible! }
9... O-O 10. Bd3 Nh5
