{ And the problem is that White is now ready to meet dxc4 with bxc4, gaining all the control in the center. }
9... dxc4
{ The only way for Black to try to develop or at least open up some diagonals for the c8-bishop. The downside is that we give up any hope of fighting for control in the center. }
10. bxc4 e5 11. d5
{ White gains a lot of space! With still a lot of pieces on the board, it will be a big challenge for Black to find good squares for their pieces. }
11... Nb8 12. Qe3
{ With a big space advantage but also in development. Look at Black's pieces: almost all of them are still on the last rank... This can't be good! }
