{ Our strategy is simple. We want to take control of the center first and then solve the problem of the c6-knight that has to be rerouted to a better position. }
11. e3 Bf5
{ Black's development is complete! There is only one problem in our position: the knight on c6. It has served its purpose by not allowing White's knight to e5. Now we should try to bring it to a more harmonious place @@StartBracket@@d6 for example@@EndBracket@@. }
12. Rfc1 a6 13. a3 Na7 { Again rerouting our knight. } 14. Ne5 c6 15. b4
{ White is attempting a pawn minority attack on the queenside, but it's not so easy to make it happen, as the logical Rab1, a4, b5 follow-up does not work because our bishop controls the b1-square. }
15... Nc8
{ And we should again continue with Nd6, Nfe4, f6 and h5-h4. At the same time, we have to keep an eye on the queenside. }
