10... b6 11. Qxc4 Nb4
{ And now we see why it wasn't exactly the greatest idea for White to delay castling. Now, if White castles short, we have Ba6 when we win the exchange. }
12. e5
{ This move weakens the light squares, allowing us a nice outpost on d5. }
12... Nfd5 13. Nxd5
{ White must take if they want to castle anytime soon. Ba6 was a very unpleasant threat. }
13... Nxd5 14. O-O a5
{ Black's position is fine now. We have a great outpost for our knight on d5, the bishop can develop to either b7 or a6. Of course, our c7 pawn might become a weakness, but so can White's pawn on d4. If White tries to create some inconveniences for our bishop by playing Qc6, we can always force the queen to move away with Rb8 followed by Bb7. }
